                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440701-name-353" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440701-name-353" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440701-name-353" type="surname" value="STEPHENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440701-name-353" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES STEPHENSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in partnership with Daniel Hayes, and live in Arbour-terrace, Commercial-road. At half-past eleven o'clock on the 29th of June, I was in the shop—I saw the prisoner and two other girls about the window—I was serving another customer—they put their faces close to the window, and then went round the corner—some hoots hung on a hook out<lb></lb>side, the prisoner came and stood with her shawl out, and one of the others, who got away, unhooked them—the prisoner took them under her arms—I followed, and took her two doors off—she begged me to let her go—these are the boots.</p>
